From: Sven Dröge <sven.droege@...>
Date: 10-19-01 13:17:27
Subject: @{b}Re: Gadgets & Mouse@{ub}

Hi,

perhaps someone is interested in my solution of this problem. The source
uses some custom libraries (LotanLibs), but you will understand it for sure.
Here it is:

; -- Main routine
; piktogramme : a variable that holds the number of gadgets
Repeat
  ev.l = WaitEvent : a$=Inkey$ : key = RawKey : Format ""

Select ev
Case #IDCMP_MOUSEMOVE
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Use Window #FUNCTIONS
    mx = WMouseX : my = WMouseY : i = 0 : *bgad.Gadget=0
    Repeat
      *gad.Gadget = GTGadPtr(#FUNCTIONS,i)
      gx = *gad\LeftEdge
      gy = *gad\TopEdge
      gw = *gad\Width
      gh = *gad\Height
      If (mx>gx) AND (mx<gx+gw) AND (my>gy) AND (my<gy+gh)
        *bgad.Gadget = *gad
      EndIf
      i + 1
    Until (*bgad<>0) OR (i>piktogramme)

    If (*bgad <> *ogad.Gadget)
      *win.Window = Peek.l(Addr Window(#FUNCTIONS))
      DrPort *win\RPort

      If (*bgad>0)
        gx = *bgad\LeftEdge
        gy = *bgad\TopEdge
        gw = *bgad\Width-1
        gh = *bgad\Height-1
        DrBevel gx,gy,gx+gw,gy+gh,1,2
      EndIf

      If (*ogad>0)
        gx = *ogad.Gadget\LeftEdge
        gy = *ogad\TopEdge
        gw = *ogad\Width-1
        gh = *ogad\Height-1
        DrBox gx,gy,gx+gw,gy+gh,0
      EndIf
      *ogad = *bgad
    EndIf

    FlushEvents #IDCMP

CASE #IDCMP_GADGETDOWN
;...
; ...etc...

Greetings to you,
Sven Dröge


