It is a bug in the NCS.

>implemented everything with pure os functions but it still happens. And I
>do use the #LISTVIEWIDCMP tag etc.

#LISTVIEWIDCMP is not a tag, you need to combine it with your IDCMP flags when 
you open the window.

>My code does this:
>
>DEFTYPE .Window *w0, *w5, *w9
>DEFTYPE .IntuiMessage *idcmp0, *idcmp5, *idcmp9
>
>signals.l=Wait_(*w0\UserPort|*w5\UserPort|*w9\UserPort)

You're not waiting correctly, it should be e.g. (1 LSL *w0\UserPort\mp_SigBit) 
not just the userport in each case.

>      Select *idcmp0\Class

You shouldn't really do this, ini case your program takes a while to do the 
processing for anything. You are supposed to reply as quickly as possible to 
the message. In reality, this means taking a copy of the fields you are 
interested in and then doing a reply.

One last thing, how are you opening your windows? When I was trying to find 
the bug in the NCS I was doing different combinations of NCS and OS code, but 
I cannot remember the results. You might still get this problem if you open 
the window with NCS code and then use OS code to process the messages.

