>Yeah yeah ;-) What`s in a name, trust me it`s done correctly(well otherwise 
it
>wouldn`t compile anyways :)

OK, I'll trust you on that one :)

>C=>My code does this:
>C=>
>C=>DEFTYPE .Window *w0, *w5, *w9
>C=>DEFTYPE .IntuiMessage *idcmp0, *idcmp5, *idcmp9
>C=>
>C=>signals.l=Wait_(*w0\UserPort|*w5\UserPort|*w9\UserPort)
>
>C=You're not waiting correctly, it should be e.g. (1 LSL
>C=*w0\UserPort\mp_SigBit)
>
>C=not just the userport in each case.
>
>I see and what does 1 LSL do?

LSL means Logically Shift Left. What it does is shift the value on the left 
hand side of LSL to the left by the number of binary places specified in the 
right hand side of LSL, e.g.

1 LSL 2 = %0000000001 LSL 2 = %0000000100
1 LSL 15 = %000000000000001 LSL 15 = %000000000000001

You need to do this because the Wait_ command takes a signal mask. To get the 
signal mask for a Window's message port (or any other message port) is to 
shift the value 1 to the left by the number of places specified in the SigBit 
field of the message port.

>C=>      Select *idcmp0\Class
>
>C=You shouldn't really do this, in case your program takes a while to do the
>C=processing for anything. You are supposed to reply as quickly as possible 
to
>
>C=the message. In reality, this means taking a copy of the fields you are
>C=interested in and then doing a reply.
>
>Ok, I have done this and it now does work correctly:
>
>  NVWait
>
>  ;signals.l=Wait_(1 LSL *w9\UserPort\mp_SigBit)
>    *idcmp0=GT_GetIMsg_(*w0\UserPort)
>    *idcmp0_=*idcmp0
>    GT_ReplyIMsg_(*idcmp0)

You still need to take a copy of the fields, not just the pointer. Something 
like this (if you want to copy all the fields - you could just copy them 
individually):

DEFTYPE.IntuiMessage *idcmp0, imsg0 ; Note, no pointer for the second one

;NVWait ; Not needed if you are doing a "Wait_"

; This should all be on one line
sigmask.l = (1 LSL *w0\UserPort\mp_SigBit) | (1 LSL *w5\UserPort\mp_SigBit) | 
(1 LSL *w9\UserPort\mp_SigBit) |

signals.l=Wait_(sigmask)

If signals & (1 LSL *w0\UserPort\mp_SigBit)
  *idcmp0 = GT_GetIMsg_(*w0\UserPort)
  While *idcmp0
    CopyMem_ *idcmp0,&imsg0,SizeOf.IntuiMessage
    GT_ReplyIMsg_ *idcmp0

    Select imsg0\Class
      Case #IDCMP_CLOSEWINDOW
        ; etc
    End Select
    *idcmp0 = GT_GetIMsg_(*w0\UserPort)
  Wend
EndIf

If signals & (1 LSL *w5\UserPort\mp_SigBit)
  ; Like above but for window 5
EndIf

If signals & (1 LSL *w9\UserPort\mp_SigBit)
  ; Like above but for window 9
EndIf

