Hi there, ditud@...

On 31-Oct-01, you said:

d>   I have a problem with MUIString gadgets. I created MUIString but I can't
d> write a working notification to read the string contents. I tried with
d> MUINotify and MUINotifyApp but it didn't work. Can some one send me some
d> examples how to create a good notification to read the MUI gadgets
d> (especially String). I would be very greateful. Thank you for HELP.

In normal circumstances, you don't actually need notification of a string gadget
in MUI. MUI and EFMUILib take care of the string contents themselves.

I'm going to make a couple of assumptions. 1. that you've created the gadget
using

MUIString obj no.,"String contents",Maxlen

TBH, I usually use MUIString obj no,"",maxlen and set the string contents
separately, but whichever works for you.

The second assumption is that the string object is part of a GUI which will have
something like an "OK" button, and that you have correctly set up the
notification on that button, AND that you are not concerned with the string
contents until the button is pressed. If so, your code would look something
like this:-

;MUI intialisiation stuff, including any other gadgets. The obj numbers in the
example are for demonstration purposes only, and you should replace them as
your application requires.

;The following constant can be anything you choose, as long as the number is
unique, and you define it at the start of your prog

#ID_OK=10

MUIString 10,"",64
MUISimpleButton 11,"OK"

;Rest of MUI objects.

MUIAddObjsHGroup 12,10,11 ;You would of course use AddObjsVGroup if it's a
vertical                               ;group and include all objects in the
group as required.

;Finish your MUI stuff, including initialising the window.

MUINotifyApp 11,#MUIA_Pressed,0,#ID_OK

;Then, in you main loop, after you've opened the window

ev.l=MUIWaitEvent
Select ev
    Case #ID_OK
    mystring$=MUIGetString(11)

;stick the rest of your stuff here

End Select

;The string contents will now be found in mystring$

You can set the string contents using MUISetString 11,NewString$

If you do want mui to react everytime the string contents change (unlikely), let
me know. I'm sure I can figure out a way using the #MUIV_EveryTime flag.

Regards



