There is no mistake in the code, as I get the same effect here. The mistake is 
in the way you think QBlit works. It draws the shape with the correct cookie 
mode (i.e. no block around it) but when you unqueue the shapes, they are 
removed and replaced with solid colour 0 blocks - this is what creates the 
effect of a black block around the shape.

You'd either need to manually replace the background after UnQueue, or use 
BBlits which do that automatically.

