@NODE "mail_56" " RE: Sprites - Display Library "
From: David McMinn <dave@...>
Date: 10-15-01 19:10:13
Subject: @{b}RE: Sprites - Display Library@{ub}

Hi Jason,

>I know I've asked before but no-one has replied and I really need help.
>Is there anyway at all to use the infrontb and infrontf with the AGA
>display library version of dual playfield or another way to allow sprites
>infront of and behind the two seperate layers.

Are you definately sure that InFrontx does not work with the displaylibrary? I 
had a quick look at the docs and from what I remember of the sprite/playfield 
priority hardware it should not matter that you use the displaylibrary (i.e. 
infrontx would just write to the custom chips for the sprite priority).

I've just had a look at the hardware RKRM and OK, it might not work, but make 
sure you have tried it in case it does :)

If you want to do it manually, you can:

Write/Poke a word to BPLCON2 (address $dff104)

Bits 15-7 should be all 0's
Bit 6 is the playfield 2 priority (when set to 1, pf1 shows in front of pf2 - 
if they have the same priority)
Bits 5-3 are the pf2 priority with respect to the sprites
Bits 2-0 are the pf1 priority with respect to the sprites

Values for playfield priorities against sprites (leftmost items show at the 
front, rightmost items are at the back):

000 pf   sp01 sp23 sp45 sp67
001 sp01 pf   sp23 sp45 sp67
010 sp01 sp23 pf   sp45 sp67
011 sp01 sp23 sp45 pf   sp67
100 sp01 sp23 sp45 sp67 pf

pf is playfield, spxy is sprites x and y

So for example, poking a value of %0000000001010000 would give you an order of

pf1 sp01 sp23 pf2 sp45 sp67

Poking %000000001000000 would give you

pf2 pf1 sp01 sp23 sp45 sp67

I don't think the displaylibrary would reset this each frame, but you never 
know. You could always set this up as a customstring at the start of your 
display to get around that problem if it exists.

